Class Maze

    • Method Detail

      • getStart

        public int[] getStart()
        The getStart method is used to find the start of the maze. It begins by searching the west wall and then continues to check clockwise until an entrance is found.
        Returns:
        The return is an int array with 2 values. The values represent the beginning of the maze.

      • getEnd

        public int[] getEnd()
        The getEnd method is used to find the end of the maze. It begins by searching the east wall and then continues to check clockwise until an entrance is found.
        Returns:
        The return is an int array with 2 values. The values represent the end of the maze.

        x - The param x is which array in the 2d array to search.

        Returns:
        The return is the string in the given position.

      • RecursiveMazeRunner

        public boolean RecursiveMazeRunner​(int currentX,
                                   int currentY,
                                   int endX,
                                   int endY)
        The RecursiveMazeRunner method is used to find the path to the end of the maze using a recursive back tracking. The tests are all contained in try blocks used to catch out of bounds exceptions.
        Parameters:
        currentX - the currentX is the current array in the 2d array that was checked.
        currentY - the currentY is the current position in the array that was checked.
        endX - The endX is the array in the 2d array that the end is located.
        endY - The endY is the position in the array that the end is located.
        Returns:
        The return is the boolean value true if the end was found.
